In summary these are cheese movies, but they were perfect to show to my innocent children (7-11 years old), clean, fun movies that were enjoyed by the family.

Journey 2 is not nearly as good.  the father character (who flies the plane) is particularly annoying.
So I would probably rate Journey 1 as a 3, Journey 2 as a 2.

Both movies take Jules Vern classics and add a modern day twist. In the first movie "Journey to the Center of the Earth" we have the volcano in Iceland and people go down into it and come out a volcano in the end, other than that the classic novel is not really followed.  It is a fun movie and enjoyable.  Journey Two is based on the Vern novel, Mysterious Island.  There is not much in common with the book, other than a reference to Captain Nemo and they end up on the Nautilus.  Michael Cain add some class to the movie.  As a tow pack it is a good value and makes a fun Saturday.

This movie set featuring both Journey movies are well worth the price. They are each on their own bluray disc so you don't have to worry about loss of quality.

The first movie journey to the center of the earth sets the story for the main character who is the boy searching for his father. In the second movie the boy used govnerment hacked into government equip basically to help get a Morse code cryptogphic like message, which turns out was from his grandfather who was trapped with no way off the mysterious island.

If you liked either of these movies and haven't seen both or just looking for both these movies this set is the way to go. Just make sure you have a bluray player for the bluray discs and have a great movie night full of adventure.

Although these movies are based on Jules Verne's books (Journey To The Center Of The Earth & The Mysterious Island), they really are completely different stories. Still, very entertaining and updated for a more (family) fun version. Plus, the Dolby sound and 3D is outstanding making you feel like you are really there.

Journey to the Center of the Earth was really enjoyable with the best 3D effects while Journey 2 - The Mysterious Island was entertaining but the storyline was lacking as well as the 3D effects. Both movies have really good sound.

I'm happy to have these movies in my collection and will enjoy seeing them again and sharing the experience.
